I visited this establishment for the first time and had an interesting experience.  I called ahead to order, and spoke with a pleasant person on the other end of the line. When I arrived the same person greeted me and advised me it would be a few moments before my food was ready. I was asked to have a seat at an empty table.  I sat down and watched her professionally handle the other customers and  noticed 2 Asian men working behind the counter. 1 was bagging the food as the it came out and the other was closing out tabs for the waitress.  While I'm waiting the place starts to clear out and quiet down. A couple walks in and asks for a table.  The supervisor looks at me and asks if I could give my seat to them.  I said fine and asked if my order had come out.  Instead of answering or checking he insisted I sit close behind one of the few tables with people finishing up their dinner.  I declined and sat another table.   He tells me I need to get up cause he may need the table. I looked at him and then at the other empty tables in the restaurant and told him no. He stomped off with an attitude without once again checking to see if my food had been brought out.  I sat at the table for 5 minutes and was about to demand a refund when the manager finally checked one of the bags and gave it to another customer then finally asked for my name and saw that my food had been out during the whole altercation.  He didn't apologize but instead put my food on the table and walked away. I was almost livid at that point and when getting up to grab my food was asked by the very busy waitress if everything was okay.  I told her not and she apologized on behalf of her supervisor and promised the service was never like that.  Tonight was my first and last time going to that establishment, not only was the service horrible but the food was bland as well.  I am very sorry I skipped out on going to my usual place for Pho.
